CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 10, 1945, pg. 15 reads: "Good Hunting - The Lawrenceville Sporting Club displays a portion of the results of a one-night hunting trip near Greece City, Butler County. Three raccoons, three 'possums, eight rabbits, and three squirrels were bagged.  Left to right: Foster Pickett, Jesse Stevens, Arthur Richardson, holding his dogs; Charlie Richardson, Joseph Jenkins and Comar Patterson, kneeling in center forefront. - Harris Photo.
TitMainTitle: Hunters Jesse Stevens holding dead rabbits and Charlie Richardson holding raccoons, standing in Harris studio
